race.comment: BAREFOOT ZULU (8) boasts a strong record this journey with seven wins and two minors from 14 tries. Comes off a (28.94) win last time, scoring by 3 lengths in a Special conditions race over 515m at this track. Makes strong appeal on best. PAW OSWALD (4) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 3 lengths at this track in a handy 29.27 beating Ethanol Secret. The form from his last run stacks up well. Expected to measure up again. COME TO PARTY (2) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 2.75 lengths at this track in a handy 29.46 beating He Shines. Can make it back-to-back wins. AMRON MICK (1) has a solid strike rate at this distance. Something for the Multiples: ASTON RAYNER (7)
